  "description": [
    "Attempt to Prohibit Wartime Immigration Expected in House By the Associated Press Legislation to repeal the Chi nese Exclusion Act was steered today into the critical amend ment stage with signs that op ponents would try to stop all immigration to this country for the duration of the war Chairman Dickstein of the Immi gration Committee said he expected amendments to halve present immi grant quotas as well as to bar all immigration The House wrangled for hours yesterday over the bill that would allow 105 Chinese a year to enter the United States and become clti aens Proponents declared the bill would demonstrate United States Chinese friendship providing a foundation which would help estab lish democracy in the Orient after the war They said it also would help counteract Japanese propa ganda that the exclusion laws show an insincerity toward the Chinese Representative Gossett Democrat of Texas defined the measure as the mast inexpensive investment in world peace that had yet been pro posed Opponents told the House it would be the beginning of a break down of United States immigration laws They said it would not accomplish Its intended purposeto place Chi nese on an immigration basis equal"
  ],
